#: addons/win_cond_military_influence.wad/functions.lua:197
msgid "Calculation method"
msgstr "Berekens-Aard"

#: addons/win_cond_military_influence.wad/functions.lua:198
msgid "The final score is a weighted geometric mean of four scores:"
msgstr ""

#: addons/win_cond_military_influence.wad/functions.lua:199
msgid "the total owned area"
msgstr ""

#: addons/win_cond_military_influence.wad/functions.lua:200
msgid "the sum of conquer areas of military sites"
msgstr ""

#: addons/win_cond_military_influence.wad/functions.lua:201
msgid "the total soldier statistics score"
msgstr ""

#: addons/win_cond_military_influence.wad/functions.lua:202
msgid "the total effective strength of soldiers in military sites"
msgstr ""

#: addons/win_cond_military_influence.wad/functions.lua:203
msgid ""
"The areas are counted with half weight. That means that first the area score "
"is calculated as the square root of the product of the two partial area "
"scores, then the final score is the third root of the product of the area "
"score and the two partial soldier scores."
msgstr ""

#: addons/win_cond_military_influence.wad/functions.lua:207
msgid ""
"The soldier statistics assigns a score to each soldier between 1 and 20 "
"depending on the sum of training levels, using a quadratic formula. Please "
"note that soldiers on roads and ships are not counted in the calculation "
"because of technical limitations."
msgstr ""

#: addons/win_cond_military_influence.wad/functions.lua:210
msgid ""
"The theoretical effective strength is calculated from the actual battle "
"values:"
msgstr ""

#: addons/win_cond_military_influence.wad/functions.lua:212
msgid "strength = a * h / (1 - d / 100) / (1 - e / 100) / 10000000"
msgstr ""

#: addons/win_cond_military_influence.wad/functions.lua:213
msgid "(a: average attack, h: health, d: defense, e: evade)"
msgstr ""

#: addons/win_cond_military_influence.wad/functions.lua:223
msgid ""
"The effective strength of the soldiers is different for each tribe. It is "
"between around 2.7 for rookies and around 30 for heroes for the official "
"tribes."
msgstr ""

#: addons/win_cond_military_influence.wad/functions.lua:227
#, lua-format
msgid "Effective strength of soldiers of the %s tribe:"
msgstr ""

#: addons/win_cond_military_influence.wad/functions.lua:230
#, lua-format
msgid "Rookie: %.2f"
msgstr "Snöttbaart: %.2f"

#: addons/win_cond_military_influence.wad/functions.lua:231
#, lua-format
msgid "Hero: %.2f"
msgstr "Held: %.2f"

#: addons/win_cond_military_influence.wad/functions.lua:241
msgid "Rationale"
msgstr ""

#: addons/win_cond_military_influence.wad/functions.lua:242
msgid ""
"The total area and the soldier statistics are meant to be the same as the "
"corresponding values in the general statistics, with the mentioned "
"limitation of the soldier score. The military site scores are meant to "
"measure the actual military strength in case of battles."
msgstr ""

#: addons/win_cond_military_influence.wad/functions.lua:246
msgid ""
"Using the geometric mean of the two partial area scores means that guarded "
"areas are worth more than unguarded areas, and new buildings that expand "
"your territory are worth more than ones in already guarded areas. Similarly, "
"soldiers in military sites are worth more than ones in warehouses."
msgstr ""

#: addons/win_cond_military_influence.wad/functions.lua:250
msgid ""
"Two kinds of soldier points are used because the effective strength makes "
"comparison between different tribes more realistic, but the soldier "
"statistics rewards training more."
msgstr ""

#: addons/win_cond_military_influence.wad/functions.lua:253
msgid ""
"The area score gets less weight than the soldier score because it is usually "
"much easier, faster and cheaper to expand your territory than to train your "
"soldiers, but it is the strength of your army that decides battles in the "
"end, so a strong army can easily take large territories from a weak one."
msgstr ""

